TY  - JOUR
AU  - Morgan, Donald P.
AU  - Rime, Bertrand
AU  - Strahan, Philip E.
T1  - Bank Integration and State Business Cycles*
PY  - 2004
Y1  - 2004/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/0033553042476161
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 119
IS  - 4
SP  - 1555
EP  - 1584
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We investigate how integration of bank ownership across states has affected economic volatihty within states. In theory, bank integration could cause higher or lower volatility, depending on whether credit supply or credit demand shocks predominate. In fact, year-to-year fluctuations in a state's economic growth fall as its banks become more integrated (via holding companies) with banks in other states. As the bank linkages between any pair of states increase, fluctuations in those two states tend to converge. We conclude that interstate banking has made state business cycles smaller, but more alike.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/0033553042476161
ER  - 



